definition: to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be

sentences.english: By 1958 the government had closed all visible churches.
sentences.chinese: 及至1958年，政府関闭所有有形的教会。

sentences.english: You could feel it in the air. It was tangible almost.
sentences.chinese: 你可以感觉到那种氛围，它几乎是有形的。
这种体验几乎是有形的。

sentences.english: The situs test also applies in relation to tangible movable property.
sentences.chinese: 财产所在地规则同样适用于有形动产。

sentences.english: The US-Anglo "special relationship" is intangible, and the Cold War is tangible.
sentences.chinese: 美英“特殊关系”是无形的，而冷战是有形的。

sentences.english: Because of its non-tangible form, so we never can not control it.
sentences.chinese: 由于其非有形的形式，所以我们永远也无法控制它。

sentences.english: Ancient Chinese painting on blank to intangible manifestations visible.
sentences.chinese: 中国古代画论的空白，以无形表现有形。
他把它们称为“不可或缺化”和“有形化”。

sentences.english: The Christians is called upon to make his material possessions immaterial.
sentences.chinese: 基督徒蒙召为的是将他拥有的有形财富变成无形的。

sentences.english: Tourism is a service-based industry. It has a number of tangible and intangible components.
sentences.chinese: 旅游业属服务行业，有若干有形和无形的成分。

sentences.english: Indian macaque with a bonnet-like tuft of hair.
sentences.chinese: 有形如帽子样簇毛的印度猕猴。

sentences.english: Part of estimating ROI is determining both tangible and intangible (less quantifiable) benefits.
sentences.chinese: 估计的投资回报由有形的和无形的收益决定。

sentences.english: They can also provide you with tangible proof of his infidelity .
sentences.chinese: 他们还可以向你提供有形的，证明了他的不忠。

sentences.english: For in Him dwells all the fullness of the Godhead bodily.
sentences.chinese: 因为神格一切的丰满，都有形有体的居住在基督里面。

sentences.english: Jigs physically limit and control the path of the cutting tool.
sentences.chinese: 钻模有形地限制和控制钻削刀具的路径。

sentences.english: Copyright is created in a work once it is fixed into a tangible medium of expression.
sentences.chinese: 一旦作品成为有形的表达形式，版权即已形成。

definition: to flow/to circulate/to go from place to place/to be mobile/(of assets) liquid
